    "It is thus moral competence, not merely doing the right thing (so far), that we are interested in if we want reliably moral FMSs.",
    "1 Third, a short note on this notion of a 'range of situations'.",
    "This range could, in principle, be very wide (e.g.",
    "all actions that full moral agents would be able to perform morally), or very restricted (e.g.",
    "all actions within a clearly limited domain, such as how to distribute medical resources in a given hospital)."
